Preheat your oven to 220°C. Pop the @diced chicken thigh{210%g} in a #mixing bowl{} and add a drizzle of @oil{}, the @honey{15%ml} and the @Caribbean style Jerk{2}(to taste). Season with a good pinch of @salt{pinch}. Stir together well to coat the chicken in the flavours, then cover with #clingfilm{} and set aside in the fridge.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and chop into small pieces. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Roughly chop the @medium tomato{2}(roughly chopped) into small chunks. Zest the @lime{1} then chop into wedges. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Lay out the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer and drizzle with a little @oil{}. Season with @salt{pinch} then set aside.

Put a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil) and add the @desiccated coconut{25%g}. Toast, stirring, until golden.

> TIP: Watch the coconut like a hawk - it burns easily! Tip into a #small bowl{} - keep the pan!

Wipe out the pan and return to high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. When hot, add the chicken, all its marinade and the pepper. Stir-fry until the chicken is browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> TIP: Adjust the heat if necessary, but don't be scared of keeping it high - you want the chicken to get nice and charred!

Stir through half the sweetcorn, lower the heat to medium-low and cook, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile bake the tortillas on the top shelf of your oven until golden and just crisp, ~{4-5%minutes}. Pop the @soured cream{150%ml} into a small bowl and stir through half the toasted coconut and half the lime zest. Season with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{to taste}. In a large bowl, combine the tomato, remaining sweetcorn, half the coriander and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{to taste}.

Stir the remaining lime zest through the jerk chicken.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed.

Pop the tortillas on your plates and top with a helping of jerk chicken. Dollop the coconut crema all over and serve the tomato salad alongside. Finish with a scattering of the remaining coconut and coriander all over, and the remaining lime wedges. Enjoy!